The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India sweep past China

 Sania Mirza in action on Thursday 

Hyderabad: Hosts India and Taiwan blanked China and Philippines 3-0, respectively, in the opening group ties of the Asian Hopman Cup mixed team event on Thursday. 

India got off to a solid start in group A after Sania Mirza beat Shuai Zhang 6-2, 6-2 and Rohan Bopanna brushed aside Mao-Xin Gong 6-3, 6-2. The duo then wrapped up the mixed doubles 6-2, 6-4. 

In group B, Taiwans Shuan Hwang eased past Czarina Arevalo 6-0, 6-2 in the womens singles before teammate Ti Chen beat Patrick Tierro 6-2, 4-6, 6-4. The pair then won the mixed doubles 7-5, 6-4. 

Meanwhile, Germanys Nicolas Kiefer and Martina Mueller will replace South Korea at the Hopman Cup in Perth, the ITF said on Thursday. 

 (Reuters) 




